01_getting_started.html.body:
Getting Started
Dependencies
Vonic has several dependencies, make sure you have introduced them before your awesome work.

vue.js
vue-router.js
axios.js (Vue's offcial recommendation for Ajax)
ionic.css

CDN
You can access to the latest versions of the resources via unpkg/vonic

current stable version is v1.1.2











Hello World
Now, it's time to make a Hello-World with Vonic. Online Demo Here.
Remember? Vonic is a framework for SPA (Single Page Application). So what we talk about here, is not to write a single page, but a skeleton of SPA.
Thanks to vonic, it's will be done in only 4 steps.
1.Make a Mount Point


2.Write Page Components
const Index = {
  template: `





             About



  `,
  data() {
    return { msg: 'Hello, World!' }
  }
}

const About = {
  template: `


        Nothing Here.


  `
}

3.Define Routes
const routes = {
  '/': {
    component: Index
  },

  '/about': {
    component: About
  }
}

4.Start Your App
Vue.use(Vonic.app, {
  routes: routes,
  defaultRouterUrl: '/'
})
Yes! That's all.

